                            <p>
                                As soon as Fred lay his eyes on Andrea he knew she was special. It only took her half an hour to prove it. Coming to his aid after a vertically challenged doorman took a disliking to him. He knew she was the one.<br><br>
                                From that moment her dazzling smile and cheeky Nordic sense of humour have kept Fred out of trouble ever since.
                            </p>
                            <div class="buttons is-centered">
                                <a class="button" href="mailto:andreafors_87&#64;hotmail.com" title="Email Andrea">
                                    <span class="icon is-small">
                                        <i class="far fa-envelope"></i>
                                    </span>
                                </a>
                                <a class="button" href="https://www.instagram.com/horsepowergirl87/" title="Visit Andrea's Instagram">
                                    <span class="icon">
                                        <i class="fab fa-instagram"></i>
                                    </span>
                                </a>
                                <a class="button" href="https://www.facebook.com/horsepowergirl87" title="Visit Andrea's Facebook">
                                    <span class="icon">
                                        <i class="fab fa-facebook-f"></i>
                                    </span>
                                </a>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="column is-6 margin-top-one-hundred">
                <div class="card is-shady">
                    <div class="card-content">
                        <div class="media">
                            <div class="media-center">
                                <img class="author-image" src="~/Content/images/frederick-james.jpg" alt="Portrait of Frederick James">
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="content article-body margin-top-one-hundred">
                            <h2>Frederick James</h2>
                            <p>
                                Frederick with the many middle names (one of them being Kingdom after Isambard Brunel who basically designed the couples’ hometown Bristol) is a warm-hearted man with a wicked sense of humour.<br><br>
                                His ability to make Andrea laugh and his rugged good looks are what made her fall head over heels in the first place.
                            </p>
                            <div class="buttons is-centered">
                                <a class="button" href="mailto:fredjsam87&#64;live.co.uk" title="Email Fred">
                                    <span class="icon is-small">
                                        <i class="far fa-envelope"></i>
                                    </span>
                                </a>
                                <a class="button" href="https://twitter.com/freddie2025" title="Visit Fred's Instagram">
                                    <span class="icon">
                                        <i class="fab fa-twitter"></i>
                                    </span>
                                </a>
                                <a class="button" href="https://www.facebook.com/freddie2025" title="Visit Fred's Instagram">
                                    <span class="icon">
                                        <i class="fab fa-facebook-f"></i>
                                    </span>
                                </a>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="columns features">
            <div class="column is-12 margin-top-neg-sixty">
                <div class="card is-shady">
                    <div class="card-content">
                        <div class="content">
                            <h2>Our Story</h2>
                            <p class="is-size-6">
                                January 26th is a big deal to any Australian. It marks the anniversary of the first British fleet to arrive at Port Jackson in New South Wales and is celebrated each year as Australia Day.
                                For Andrea and Fred, despite not being even remotely Australian, this day is indeed a big deal. It was on the day of thong rafting and messy barbecues that they met in 2014.<br><br>
                                It was in a noisy beer garden that they locked eyes for the first time. And it was definitely love at first sight. For the coming three weeks, these two lovebirds were inseparable. Until Fred had to leave Australia for home soil that is.
                                However, the two had seen something in one another that they had never seen in anyone else and swore that they would stick together. And so they did.
                                For the next 4 years, their relationship was all about trying to overcome immigration laws and other obstacles dead set on keeping them separated.
                                In the end, love conquered all and they settled happily in Fred’s native England where they are currently planning their upcoming wedding.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
